# This project intentionally does not use Prettier.
#
# Formatting is governed by ESLint + .editorconfig (tabs, compact single-line
# objects), and several modules are pinned by the eslint `max-lines` rule
# (see eslint.config.mts). Prettier's default print width reflows the repo's
# compact style across multiple lines, inflating those modules past their
# pinned caps and breaking `npm run lint`. Opt out of Prettier entirely so any
# editor/automation that auto-runs `prettier --write` leaves files untouched.
**
